e point IMO. His visions, based on which in a=C2=A0totally =\r\nnon-calculating, guileless and childlike manner, he would proclaim the past=\r\n lives of various disciples, had a strong grain of truth that actualized in=\r\n a reasonable accurate manner at a much later date. Let me give one example=\r\n. One day Sri Ramakrishna was sitting in his room around evening when he sa=\r\nw a vision of Lord Krishna with another young boy, dressed like a cowherd, =\r\nstanding in the middle of a lotus.=C2=A0 The next day he saw the exact same=\r\n boy come to Dakshineshwar. Incidentally the boy&#39;s name was Rakhal, meaning=\r\n cowherd. Sri Ramakrishna told him that he was in a previous birth, one of =\r\nthe cowherd companions of Sri Krishna in Vrndavana! Later, many decades lat=\r\ner, when Sri Ramakrishna himself had left his physical body, Rakhal went on=\r\n to become a teriffic saint of very very high caliber named Swami Brahmanan=\r\nda and one of the greatest devotees of Lord\n Krshna. His spiritual fulfillm=\r\nent came through worship of Lord Krshna and the study of the Gita. In his l=\r\nast years, he would see and interact with Krshna at all times and hours bef=\r\nore his own death he saw Lord Krshna come to him and take his hand and call=\r\n him back to his own realm. Within hours of this experience he died. The po=\r\nint being, the vision that Sri Ramakrishna saw many decades ago,at a time w=\r\nhen Rakhal himself had no clue of his potential and his specific path, all =\r\nproved correct and accurate. Ramakrishna himself was not alive to see that =\r\nday,=C2=A0therefore it cannot be said e had any agenda in making those proc=\r\nlamations to Rakhal about his past life and his path. So if all this turned=\r\n out to be true in such a tremendous manner, we have no basis to say that h=\r\nis declaratoin of Rakhal&#39;s, or anyone else&#39;s=C2=A0past life was not-true. \n=\r\n=C2=A0Wwe know what imagination and visualization is. All of us have these =\r\npowers of imagination is various measures. But none of us can &#39;imagine&#39; the=\r\n future and make it happen the way we imagine it, that=C2=A0too=C2=A0on a=\r\n=C2=A0regular basis. Then it is not imagination any more. This is something=\r\n else totally. All of Sri Ramakrishna&#39;s vision proved to be 100% accurate a=\r\nt all times. Not one failed.=C2=A0 This is far=C2=A0beyond the capability o=\r\nf the human mind, imagination or visualization or whatever else we want to =\r\ncall it.\n\nAround the time when Swami Vivekananda was born, Ramakrishna one =\r\nday saw a vision in the sky. He saw a powerful bolt of lightning coming fro=\r\nm Kashi and heading towards Bengal. He saw, in his vision, the whole sky wa=\r\ns like split asunder by the power and force of that blaze of lightning. He =\r\ntold some people around him that a very powerful soul has takne birth who h=\r\nas a strong connection to Lord Shiva. Nearly twenty years after this vision=\r\n he met the future Swami Vivekananda for the first time, and as Vievakanda&#39;=\r\ns life later showed, he turned out to be=C2=A0a great Shiva devotee. \n\nLoos=\r\nely speaking one can say that the mind has many hidden abilities. But I loo=\r\nk at it differently. We are born with three koshas - annamaya (physical bod=\r\ny), pranamaya ( life-force) and manomaya (mind). Even in these, each indivi=\r\ndual with have subtle variations in the amount of influence, clarity, depth=\r\n and other things that they have at their disposal in the use of these kosh=\r\nas. This is standard knowledge. One can be born with a very roboust physica=\r\nl body that can sustain many things while anothe with a weak body. Etc. But=\r\n there is a fourth kosha which lies only as a potential. SOme yogis, by the=\r\n power of their sadhana, can develop the same. Shastras call it Vigyanamaya=\r\n.=C2=A0One of best misconcption of this age is that Vgyana means intellect =\r\nas we know it. Hardly. Even the most logically powerful, sharpest and swift=\r\nest intellect is still a working of the manomaya kosha, of course at a high=\r\n pitch. But the Vigyana is sifferent. WHen the Yogi is able\n to=C2=A0develo=\r\np and use this kosha various apparently supernatural things can manifest. T=\r\nhese appear supernatural from our point of view, but maybe just an ordinary=\r\n funtionality of that kosha=C2=A0-=C2=A0sheath - of the human organism. Is =\r\nthis Maya? It is as much Maya as you hands and your legs are.. At a very hi=\r\ngh level of development of Vigyanamaya kosha=C2=A0abilities of Trikal Darsh=\r\nan may come to the Yogi automatically. This is similar to, as I mentioned i=\r\nn the previous mail, the ability to enter the consciousness in the Karan Ja=\r\ngat. That is how some exceptional Yogis, as Vimalananda so offhandly remark=\r\ns, can see an individual and see 25=C2=A0birth in the past and 25 possible =\r\nbirths in the future! (given thecurrent momentum).\n\nNone of this is imagina=\r\ntion at all.=C2=A0 What is the use=C2=A0of this otherwise obscure kosha? On=\r\ne gets=C2=A0the clearest view of REALITY from here than from any of the oth=\r\ner koshas. That is all the bottomline is.Percieving the One Reality using=\r\n=C2=A0the various means at our disposal.=C2=A0\n\nA man like Sri Ramakrishna =\r\nis born with these koshas developed to a very=C2=A0high degree, unlike rest=\r\n of the seekers. That=C2=A0is why his visions=C2=A0almost never failed.\n\n-R=\r\negards\n=C2=A0Rajarshi\n\n\n\n\nI have a hundred lives before me yet/ To grasp th=\r\nee in, O spirit ethereal, / Be sure I will with heart insatiate/ Pursue the=\r\ne like a hunter through them all.-Sri Aurobindo\n\nFrom: Narasimha P.V.R. Rao=\r\n &lt;pvr108@...&gt;\nTo: &quot;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&quot; &lt;vedic-wisdom@yahoog=\r\nroups.com&gt; \nSent: Tuesday, 29 October 2013 7:40 AM\nSubject: [vedic-wisdom] =\r\nRe: Past life regression (Re: Mantra for protection from spirits (at nightt=\r\nime))\n\n\n\n=C2=A0 \nDear Ajit,