one in a room (field of duality) sees a rope (Self) as a snake (world appea=\r\nrance). They are all under the influence of Maya. Suppose one person in the=\r\n room makes the snake seem (to everyone in the room) to have 10 heads. Supp=\r\nose another person imagines the snake to have 10 heads and that everyone se=\r\nes 10 heads, while everyone actually sees only one head.&lt;BR clear=3Dnone&gt;&n=\r\nbsp;&lt;BR clear=3Dnone&gt;In an\n *absolute* non-dualistic sense, both are in del=\r\nusion because it is not a snake in the first place and a rope. But, in a *r=\r\nelative* dualistic sense, the latter is hallucinating and the former is mas=\r\ntering the dynamics of the room.&lt;BR clear=3Dnone&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR clear=3Dnone&gt;*&n=\r\nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp;&nbsp; *&lt;BR clear=3Dnone&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR clear=3Dnone&gt;Having said that, I must=\r\n re-emphasize that it is silly to pursue any siddhis. Seeking the ability t=\r\no make the rope that everyone sees as snake appear to have 4 heads or 10 he=\r\nads to all is a silly goal.&lt;BR clear=3Dnone&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR clear=3Dnone&gt;A true s=\r\neeker will seek the ability to always see as rope what everyone sees as sna=\r\nke. That is the only meaningful &quot;ability&quot;. During the process of acquiring =\r\nthat ability, one may get other abilities (e.g. the above one). Some seeker=\r\ns get attached to them and get stuck. Some reject them and keep progressing=\r\n.&lt;BR clear=3Dnone&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR\n clear=3Dnone&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN style=3D&quot;RIGHT=\r\n: auto&quot;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbs=\r\np;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;BR clear=3Dnone&gt;&nbsp;&lt;BR clear=3Dnone&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;=\r\n&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;When a Ramakrishna told a few of his disciples who they were i=\r\nn a past life, one might not have been able to know FOR SURE if he was corr=\r\nect or not. Nevertheless